        "meta_description": "Architecture practice Ferrier Marchetti Studio completed  CO'Met - Arena, a stadium and congress and convention centre, located at the southern entrance of Orleans, a city on the banks of the Loire River in north-central France. Co'Met dramatically changes the perception of the entrance to the metropolis of Orleans. The building conveys a great sensation of lightness inspired by the subtle and changing atmosphere of the banks of the Loire. The stadium, the convention centre and the exhibition centre come together in this large multifunctional volume creating a spectacular sequence along the south entrance of Orleans.",
